METADATA <target> <action> [params...]

Manages the metadata of a user or channel. The batch and
draft/metadata-3 capabilities must both be negotiated to
use this command. A target of "*" may be used to target
the current user. action should be one of the following:

SUB
  Subscribes to notifications for a list of keys; takes N
  additional parameters, one per key to subscribe to.
  Target must be the current user.

UNSUB
  Removes subscriptions for a list of keys; takes N
  additional parameters, one per key to unsubscribe from.
  Target must be the current user.

SUBS
  Displays the user's subscriptions; takes no additional
  parameters. Target must be the current user.

SYNC
  Displays the values for all subscribed keys on the
  target; takes no additional parameters.

GET
  Displays the values for the list of keys on the target;
  takes N additional parameters, one per key to retrieve.

LIST
  Displays the value for all keys on the target; takes no
  additional parameters.

SET
  Sets the value of the given key on the target to the
  given value; takes two additional parameters of the key
  and value, in that order. The value parameter may be
  omitted or set to the empty string to delete the key.

CLEAR
  Deletes all keys on the target; takes no additional
  parameters. Displays a list of all deleted keys.

ABORT
  Aborts an in-progress asynchronous operation; takes no
  additional parameters. LIST, SYNC, and CLEAR may be
  executed asynchronously if their output is very large,
  to avoid disconnecting the client for exceeding their
  send queue.
